The paper discusses censorship on the Internet infrastructure in India, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the potential for a government-controlled filter, which could fall under the category of cyber law and policy (cs.CY). The paper also mentions the use of IP Prefix Hijacking, which falls under the category of protocol design and analysis (cs.PF). Finally, the paper discusses the collateral damage that such censorship could cause to non-Indian ASes, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
